rComments: Awesome prof, laughs a lot which is entertaining. Grading outline is very clear, group project, midterm and final exam. Take good lecture notes. If you do a decent presentation and research paper, she'll grade you well for the group project. You can always shoot her an email to ask questions on class content.
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She explains everything slow and detailed, multiple times. So the lectures are easy to follow and understand. The prof always laughs and make you laugh which motivates you a lot. Overall amazing content and a prof. I highly recommend!

Professor Plamondon is great! I've taken a few classes with her through my University experience and when I saw she was teaching the Drugs and behaviour class I decided to take it as one of my electives because I like her teaching methods so much! She always records classes so you can go back and review material you might have missed!

She is such a sweetheart! A wonderful teacher that cares about the students experience. She is always funny and in a good mood. Really passionate about her field and the topics of the presentations were really interesting.

Dr. Plamondon is the kindest professor I've ever met. She genuinely cares about her students and strives to design the course such that they are less burdened by the course requirements. She is constantly upbeat and positive to help any student that needs help.

Dr. Plamondon knew how to make the class smile! Her energy was contagious and she was always giving students words of affirmation and motivation - which is definitely needed in graduate studies. She was always encouraging us to contact her for any reason at any time. To have her as a resource going forward is going to be so helpful! :)
Dr. Plamondon was super sweet. It was always a joy attending her lectures. Will definitely take her again in the future.
Awesome prof!! She's such a sweetheart and you can tell she cares so much about her students' success. She was really mindful about not making the course load too heavy which was great :)

Unbearable. Asked a question on a student's poster presentation, as he was answering, she interrupted saying there was more questions in the chat, and that she didn't mean to interrupt, and kept going anyways.

I found her personality intoxicating, laughed exaggeratedly to anything, which turned 30 minutes of content into 90 minutes presentations.

Takes her time to thoroughly explain some more abstract concepts. Records her live lectures so you can watch whenever, love that! If you take notes from her lectures + go over the powerpoints easy A on her exams! no surprises, taken two classes with her, just a great prof, thank you dr plamondon!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Had her for PSY2701 too and she is by far the BEST prof I've ever had. Explains things very easily and goes over concepts until you're able to understand them. She speaks pretty slowly so its easy to understand. She cares SO MUCH and really wants you to succeed. Lots of slides but you'll have to take notes while she talks. TAKE HER :)
Sweetest prof ever. Very caring and accessible.

She's the sweetest person, really cares about her students and is so accessible outside class. For the class itself, I'm the worst at biology, sometimes it's boring but I got an A because she really tries to make her exams easier for us, we also had a paper to write. Honeslty just take her class you won't regret it.

I don't know what to say, she's just AMAZING!! You can tell she really care about her students & even though classes were online, she was easily accessible by email/personal Zoom sessions if needed. 10/10!!

She's great! She makes herself laugh and it's a pretty funny. She explains the material and does extra research for questions she can't answer. Her exams aren't MC and the questions are clear! The lectures are good and well organized, everything can be found on the slides. Good prof!

She explains the material really well and she's always there to help you. The exams reflect the material in class. Just make sure you do the readings because some of the questions of the midterms come from the textbook!

It's a very biological class (considering it's psych). She is such a bright and kind person. If you read the book and powerpoints over and over, you should be good. The tests are not trick questions or anything, it's just a lot of memorizing.

She's really caring and clearly knows the subject matter. Sometimes she gets a little off topic which her jokes but she makes herself laugh and it's hard not to laugh with her. All around great person, teaches clearly and her exams reflect exactly what she teaches and what's in the textbook.

Prof. Plamondon is such a nice lady but her tests this semester we're very difficult, she asks very specific questions about difficult topics that were explained quickly and long answer questions required you to define a lot of complicated processes in very little time
Dr Plamondon is amazing! She is very funny and always does her best to make sure everyone understands and gets the best grade possible for them. Personally, I absolutely recommend Dr Plamondon!
J'ai adoré ce professeur. Elle était super intéressante et connaissait très bien sa matière. Elle aime aussi que ses étudiants réussissent et elle est plutôt drôle.

She is such a nice prof and is very passionate about drugs. Her slides replace the textbook and she responds very quickly to emails. She wants all her students to succeed. Definitely would take another one of her classes!
She has a great personality! Very friendly and caring but I was a little disappointed by the fact that she missed 2 classes and that she didn't order the textbook on time.

Excellent and funny professor.  She has a particular teaching style (she used a mafia analogy to explain DNA, love it!) and is one of the bubbliest people I have ever encountered!  Neuroscience can be complicated, but she simplifies it in a wonderful way and if you attend class, listen and do your readings, you'll do great.
J'ai beaucoup ce professeur. Elle est dévouée envers les étudiants et toujours souriante. Elle se passionne par sa matière et la communique très bien.
Very joyful prof, has never entered class without a huge smile on her face! A lot of notes are taken on the board in addition to the PowerPoints. Good teacher, just a difficult subject.

She's really amazing and have an awesome personality! Their exams are weird and kind a bit difficults because the questions are not clear sometimes and ask random question that never been presented in class. BUT She's very amazing I loved her!
She truly cares about her students and their success, she is always more than happy to answer questions and very patient,you can tell she really loves what she does. AMAZING!
THIS IS MY FAVOURITE PROF EVER. SHE IS THE BEST.

Good professor,many notes(marks) has to add to power points given. She is clear but can go too quickly on an estimated subject. Final exam in human behavior is more difficult than the others: too much material in depression few in hormone
THE ABSOLUTE BEST!

Elle n'a pas beaucoup été disponible pour ses élèves cette session. Cependant, lorsqu'on l'a rencontre, elle est vraiment à l'écoute de ceux-ci. Elle est très gentille et sait te guider dans la bonne voix. Définitivement, l'université d'Ottawa a fait un excellent choix en la prenant!! elle est  fantastique

C'est la meilleure professeur du département. Elle est extrêmement flexible face aux évaluations et elle prend énormément de temps pour être à l'écoute de ses élèves. Elle disponible en tout temps lorsqu'on a besoin d'elle. Définitivement, une des meilleures à uOttawa!

Cette prof parle avec clarete et tres fort. Elle utilise des powerpoints quelle envoi par courriel pour imprimer avant les cours. Tu doit aller au cours pour reussir et lire le livre (les grandes lignes). Beaucoup de par coeur mais la prof fait des dessin au tableau pour les visuels. Pose des questions en classe ca benefecie tous!
Decent teacher, a little quirky and fun. However, she has no office hours and doesn't give you anything to prepare for the exams (which are, thankfully, rather easy).

very funny teacher, she usually keeps the interest throughout the whole class. Helpful.  I found it was fun to go to that class just for the way she teaches.  She loves what she does and it shows. Would definitely recommend her!
Love her way of teaching. She's dynamic and very funny. She's a great teacher.

She is an awesome prof! I had a really great semester in this class. You really gotta attend class though because a big part of her exams is what she says in class! She's very animated and funny and made her class interesting
Such a good teacher. She's funny, clear and easy going.

Very knowledgeable,very fair, pretty laid back, answers to every m/c question have been given at least once in class.  whatever you do: pay attention to what she says in class, take good notes, try not to miss classes. Will definitely take another class with her

She's A Good Prof... Attending class is a serious recommendation here, the exams are a bit heavy... A LOT of "what's the true/false statement" 3 exams and she puts your best exam on 40%. Recommend but only if this a compulsory class.
